<p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/HVQRq.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/HVQRq.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>The layout of the JFrame in the picture is a GridBagLayout. The e-mail JTextfield has a gridwidth of 3. Is there any possibility to give this JTextfield a 100% width to fill the whole grid cell?</p>  <p>The fields are added dynamically. So give it a static width value width setColumns is not an option.</p>